```julia
function timezone_bumper(dt, bump = 3)
    if !isa(dt, DateTime))
        error("Input must be of type DateTime.")
    end

    return dt + convert(Dates.Hour, bump))
end
```
This function `timezone_bumper` takes a `DateTime` input and increases it by the specified `bump` hours (default is 3). It throws an error if the input is not a `DateTime`.
